Consent:
Attitudes toward helping and morality 



Study Description

 

You are invited to participate in a research study supported by Wake Forest University. If you decide to participate, you will be asked to complete some self-evaluation questions about your attitudes toward helping and personality traits. This study will take approximately 20 minutes to complete. Although we cannot tell you the specific hypotheses of the study before the end of the study, the purpose of this study is to discover how scores on the questionnaire relate to each other. 



Possible Risks or Benefits



Participating in this study does not pose any significant risk beyond that which you would normally expect to encounter during everyday life. There is a risk of possible emotional reaction to the content of the surveys, but we do not judge this risk to be more than minimal. Although we cannot promise you any direct benefit from your participation in the study, the information we gain from this study may someday be used to help others gain insight into how they typically think and act.



Compensation



As compensation for agreeing to participate in this study, you will receive $3. Due to the layout of the Qualtrics Platform, participants will not be compensated if they withdraw before completing the survey.  



Inclusion criteria



You must be 18 or older to participate in this study. 



Participation is Voluntary



Your participation in this study is completely voluntary. If you choose not to participate, you can close the survey window and be excused from the study at any time. If at any time you should feel uncomfortable about answering any questions or participating in the discussion, you can skip the question or be excused from the study at any time. You may let the study coordinator know of any questions or concerns on Prolific using the messaging system. 



Confidentiality



The researchers will take the following precautions to protect your information: The questionnaire will be conducted via Qualtrics, an online survey tool that is account-based, password protected, and protected from third-party advertising and influence. Only the researchers will know the account’s username and password, which will be stored on password-protected laptop computers. All Qualtrics accounts are hidden behind passwords and all data will be assigned a random identification number and the ID number will be deleted from the file. All physical records of data from this study will be kept in a locked cabinet in a locked room and only authorized study team members will have access to them. 



Your data will be used only for scientific purposes, and once the data is no longer needed, it will be destroyed.



Question/Concerns

 

If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact the study’s faculty member, Mason Garrison, at garrissm@wfu.edu or Student Co-Principal Investigator, Qilin Zhang, at Zhanq22@wfu.edu. If you have questions regarding your rights as a participant, contact the Office of Research and Sponsored Programs, at (336) 758-5888 or at irb@wfu.edu. The IRB number of this study is IRB00024972.
